parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stick in gear, or fail to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission sticks in second gear
the transmission fails to shift into another gear
the transmission needs to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to lose power, stick in gear, or fail to shift, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. It also results in significant financial burden on the owner due to repeated repairs.
symptoms: transmission failures within a short period of time.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the torque converter can cause the transmission to fail, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Fuel leakage from the fuel rail crossover tube can increase the likelihood of a vehicle fire, posing a significant safety risk to the driver and occupants.
symptoms: fuel leakage from the fuel rail crossover tube
fuel dripping onto the engine block
fuel spraying onto the hot manifold.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate while driving, increasing the risk of accidents or loss of control.
symptoms: The vehicle "hiccups" or jerks while driving
feels like the ignition switch is turned off or the brakes are suddenly applied

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to hazardous conditions, especially in heavy traffic.
The transmission slipping and failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become stuck in gear, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission does not want to shift out of low gear
the transmission kicks out of gear and then slams into low
the transmission fails to engage properly

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the serpentine belt can cause the loss of power steering, alternator, and other essential functions, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The tension pulley shears off from the engine block
the tensioner arm locks in full tension position
other functions powered by the serpentine belt fail.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
